variables.value: Even with help from Raimon, West Manor still lost...?\nHuh, <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>... Who are they?
If things go as planned, we'll face Royal Academy in the final.\nBut hey, if there's an upset, it could be <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>...
So it'll be <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>\nin the final, huh?
Raimon's skills and <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>'s energy should make for a good match.\nBut who's gonna win in the end, I wonder...
Ask anyone who's gonna win this year's Football Frontier,\nthey'll all say it's gonna be Raimon!
Royal Academy is powerful, no doubt.\nBut Raimon can still beat them!\nThat's what makes Raimon all the more awesome!
Next is the grand final, right?\nI'm rooting for you! Bring home that trophy!
Raimon never loses... Never ever!\nI watched the Spring Cup too.\nThey're in especially solid form this year!
It does feel like Royal Academy is Raimon's biggest rival.\nI've never seen Raimon lose, not yet...
It's a shame <FST:HARU>'s not playing...\nBut Raimon's got what it takes, I just know you guys can win!
The football club's amazing,\nespecially with stars like you in its ranks.\nYou're firing us baseball players up, too!
You can train in Raimon Stadium\nwhatever the weather... That's so cool.\nThe track team and the other clubs are all so jealous!
You guys have the grand final soon, right?\nNot that you'll need it, but all the same... Good luck out there!
You could try\nfor a sports scholarship.
Well, if your mind's set on something, I'd say just go for it.\nHaving friends to encourage and inspire you to be better\nis a great thing, too.
I'd bet the Raimon club players all want to go pro,\nor find a way to stay in the game as they grow older at least.
It's important to consider the future. But right now,\nall I can think about is Raimon's upcoming match.\nI mean, it is the Football Frontier grand final, after all!
We'll be ready come\nshowtime, I know it!
They all are!\nCan they all be my fave?
He's on the other team,\nbut... I pick <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>!
Loads of our club members are interested in the football club.\nApparently, some use martial arts when they're playing.
The sumo club's stew tastes different\ndepending on which coordinator makes it.\nThey all stick to one rule: you've gotta finish every last bite.
Noble Insight Institute and Alpine Junior High\nfaced Raimon in the grand final, right?\nBoth strong, but unlucky with the draw.
Raimon Junior High is huge...\nA design choice to strengthen its students' legs, maybe!
I wonder how long they'll keep the old football club room?\nMaybe they plan to make it a tourist spot someday?
The vending machines here sell some odd stuff...\nWait... Could they be the secret to the football club's strength?!
The old football club room... Where the legend began.\nRaimon Junior High wouldn't be what it is today\nwithout that team of 25 years ago.
Raimon Junior High and Royal Academy\nhave been fierce rivals for 25 years...\nTheir match kicked off Raimon's legendary legacy.
The old Raimon squad's legacy created today's champions.\nThey need to win the grand final and remain undefeated!
What's the club manager actually like?\nNo one ever talks about him, so I've no idea.
The club's taking <FST:HARU>'s injury pretty hard.\nDo you think the match will go okay?
First <FST:HARU>, and now Manager <LST:OTOME> is gone too.\nAnd right before the grand final... I wonder what happened.
He keeps them together... So he's probably amazing.\nProbably always thinking up ways to make them even\nbetter players.
A player had to leave the pitch, but they still won the game.\nRaimon's strong, they've got what it takes to win again.
I hear the opposition has an amazing manager or player running things.\nBut Raimon's unbeatable. If they just play as usual, they've got this.
I just think Manager <LST:OTOME> is the best.\nHe seems kind, and cool, and mature...
It's all because Manager <LST:OTOME> handled it calmly.\nThat's what true adult composure looks like...
I bet Manager <LST:OTOME> stepped back 'cause he believes in his team.\nThey'll carry that trust with them, into the grand final...
The Raimon team hasn't lost in ages.\nBack in my day, I never dreamed they'd become such a team.
How's the football club doing these days?\nThey've got way nicer facilities now. Must make training easier!
The Football Frontier's really heating up!\n<MNT:NAGUMOHARA>'s amazing run reminds me of Raimon's legendary days.
The more you look,\nthe cooler it gets!
Raimon did give them\na hand, but...
Didn't they help out in West Manor's match?\nWell, Raimon shouldn't just share their strength with other teams...
Even if you can\nsummon a Keshin...
Some schools can summon Keshin, so they rely on them.\nThat's not real strength if you ask me, though.
Show them in the next match that Raimon's the best!\nA club that's second to none!
Oh, he does that a lot.
He did? Then...\nWhy are you smiling?
